<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{9}{y}={17}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5}{x}-{6}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({2},{3}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{9}{y}={17}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}={17}-{\left({9}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{17}-{\left({9}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{\left(\frac{{{17}-{\left({9}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{5}}}}\right)}+-{6}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{5}}{{-{{5}}}}\cdot{\left({17}\right)}-\frac{{5}}{{-{{5}}}}{\left({9}\right)}{y}+-{6}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{17}-{\left({9}\right)}{y}+-{6}{y}=-{8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{y}+{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}=-{8}--{17}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{y}+{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}={9}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({9}+{\left(-{6}\right)}\right)}{y}={9}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}{y}={9}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{9}}{{3}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={3}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{9}{\left({3}\right)}={17}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}+{\left({27}\right)}={17}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}={17}-{\left({27}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5}{x}=-{10}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{10}}{{-{{5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({2},{3}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

